A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to state government,
2 so as to designate the Attorney General as an applicable elected representative who may
3 approve issuance of certain private activity bonds; to establish procedures for public notices
4 and hearings relative to such bonds; to authorize county and regional library boards and
5 community service boards to conduct teleconference meetings under certain circumstances;
6 to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to state government, is amended
10 by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
11 "50-1-14.
12 The Attorney General is designated as an applicable elected representative, as provided for
13 in 26 U.S.C. Section 147(f)(2)(E) of the Internal Revenue Code, who may approve the
14 issuance of one or more private activity bonds to finance or refinance a state charter school
15 facility after a public hearing following reasonable notice in accordance with 26 U.S.C.
16 Section 147(f) of the Internal Revenue Code and applicable state and federal rules. Within
17 60 days of the Attorney General receiving a written request for a public hearing, he or she
