44 (D) The board of trustees or other governing body of any large retirement system as
45 such term is defined in subsection (a) of Code Section 47-20-84;
46 (E) The board of trustees of any county or regional public library created pursuant to
47 Part 2 of Article 2 of Chapter 5 of Title 20; provided, however, that such meetings:
48 (i) Shall be held at a physical location with at least 50 percent of the board members
49 physically present; and
50 (ii) Shall provide one or more methods for public viewing of such meetings and
51 providing commentary at such meetings without being physically present at such
52 meetings; and
53 (F) Community service boards created pursuant to Article 1 of Chapter 2 of Title 37;
54 provided, however, that such meetings:
55 (i) Shall be held at a physical location with at least 50 percent of the board members
56 physically present; and
57 (ii) Shall provide one or more methods for public viewing of such meetings and
58 providing commentary at such meetings without being physically present at such
59 meetings.
60 (2) The participation by teleconference of members of such bodies or committees thereof
61 means full participation in the same manner as if such members were physically present.
62 In the event such teleconference meeting is a public hearing, and if fewer than a quorum
63 of the members of a body or committee thereof are physically present, then members of
64 the public shall be afforded the means to participate fully in the same manner as if such
65 members of the public were physically present."
66 SECTION 3.
67 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
